1ï¸âƒ£ What is a Channel?
A channel is a typed conduit used to send and receive data between goroutines.

ch := make(chan int)
ğŸ“Œ Used for safe communication, not shared memory.

2ï¸âƒ£ Why Channels?
âœ” Synchronization
âœ” Communication
âœ” Avoid race conditions
âœ” Follow Go proverb
â€œDo not communicate by sharing memory; share memory by communicatingâ€

3ï¸âƒ£ Channel Direction
ch <- 10      // send
x := <-ch     // receive

4ï¸âƒ£ Blocking Behavior (VERY IMPORTANT)
Send blocks until receive
Receive blocks until send
ğŸ“Œ This is synchronization.

5ï¸âƒ£ Unbuffered Channel
ch := make(chan int)

âœ” Send & receive must meet
âœ” Strong synchronization

6ï¸âƒ£ Buffered Channel

ch := make(chan int, 3)
âœ” Send blocks only when buffer full
âœ” Receive blocks when empty

7ï¸âƒ£ Channel Capacity & Length
cap(ch) // buffer size
len(ch) // current items

8ï¸âƒ£ Channel with Goroutines

go func() {
    ch <- 10
}()

fmt.Println(<-ch)

9ï¸âƒ£ Channel Deadlock (INTERVIEW FAVORITE)

