go func() {
    close(done)
}()
<-done
âœ” Zero-memory signal.

1ï¸âƒ£8ï¸âƒ£ Fan-out / Fan-in Pattern

One channel â†’ many workers
Many workers â†’ one channel
âœ” Very common interview topic.

1ï¸âƒ£9ï¸âƒ£ Channel vs Mutex (RECAP)
Channel	                        Mutex
Communication	                  Shared memory
Safer logic	                    Faster
Data flow	                      Critical section

2ï¸âƒ£0ï¸âƒ£ Common Interview Traps

âŒ Deadlock due to missing receiver
âŒ Closing channel twice
âŒ Sending on closed channel
âŒ Forgetting buffer size

Channel
A channel is a typed conduit used to safely communicate between goroutines.

Buffered vs Unbuffered
Unbuffered channels synchronize goroutines, buffered channels decouple them.

ğŸ§  Quick Memory Points
Send blocks
Receive blocks
Close by sender
Range until closed
Nil blocks forever

21ï¸âƒ£ Happens-Before Guarantee (VERY IMPORTANT)
ch <- x
y := <-ch
âœ” Write to x happens before receive
âœ” Channels provide memory visibility

ğŸ‘‰ Mutex & channels both create happens-before relation



















  
